75
00:02:58,261 --> 00:02:59,846
Hoo boy. I hope
they aren't planning

76
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:01,765
to bum‐rush a horde
of brain‐eaters.

77
00:03:01,807 --> 00:03:03,517
[SEIYA]
I doubt they're that stupid,

78
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:06,895
but even so, I'll have wiped
out those dead gas‐bags first.

79
00:03:06,937 --> 00:03:09,648
Okay, so you may be
ridiculously strong,

80
00:03:09,690 --> 00:03:12,526
but seriously! Shouldn't we
all just work together?

81
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:14,319
[SEIYA]
No way. That's dumb.

82
00:03:14,361 --> 00:03:16,363
Oh, excuse me for
thinking a little teamwork

83
00:03:16,405 --> 00:03:17,948
might be a good idea.

84
00:03:17,989 --> 00:03:19,449
[SEIYA]
There are 10,000 zombies.

85
00:03:19,491 --> 00:03:21,076
Having another one
or two hundred people

86
00:03:21,118 --> 00:03:22,703
with us is pointless.

87
00:03:22,744 --> 00:03:24,663
No need for anyone else to die,

88
00:03:24,705 --> 00:03:28,083
including those annoying
kids from Favabean.

89
00:03:28,125 --> 00:03:29,584
[RISTA]
This is new.

90
00:03:29,626 --> 00:03:32,504
Is he showing concern
for the children?

91
00:03:32,546 --> 00:03:33,964
Seiya! Ah!

92
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:36,925
Wha‐‐! When'd you get up there?

93
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:39,136
I'm heading off.
Go wait at the inn.

94
00:03:39,177 --> 00:03:40,887
Ahh? What did you say?

95
00:03:40,929 --> 00:03:43,223
And in case you think
I need your help,

96
00:03:43,265 --> 00:03:44,599
the answer's still hard pass.

97
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:45,726
[RISTA]
Whoa!

98
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:49,730
H‐Hold up. Did he reject me
when I'm a literal goddess?

99
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:52,065
Like, is this a dream?
"Hard pass"?

100
00:03:52,107 --> 00:03:55,026
That lousy, ungrateful,
selfish, glory‐hogging meathead!

101
00:03:55,068 --> 00:03:56,695
You're done‐zo!

102
00:03:56,737 --> 00:03:59,656
Ooh! I'm gonna hard pass you!

103
00:03:59,698 --> 00:04:01,491
[yells]

104
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:04,035
Order! Grant unto
the Goddess Ristarte

105
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:07,330
the gift of Flight
she should already have!

106
00:04:10,876 --> 00:04:13,545
[RISTA] This is the privilege
to unlock sublime abilities

107
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:16,381
in desperate times when
heroes need our support.

108
00:04:16,423 --> 00:04:17,382
An Order!

109
00:04:17,424 --> 00:04:20,510
A Special Measure
of the Divine Realm!

110
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:27,309
[RISTA] Hmm. Lookin' good,
if I do say so myself.

111
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,311
I'll get you and
your little abs, too.

112
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:30,270
[chuckles]

113
00:04:30,312 --> 00:04:32,564
Rista Wing!

114
00:04:32,606 --> 00:04:35,609
Never underestimate a goddess!

115
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:38,403
[SEIYA] Hmm. This is
starting to get old.

116
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:40,071
Time to go full throttle.

117
00:04:41,072 --> 00:04:42,949
Ugh! Hey, no fair!

118
00:04:42,991 --> 00:04:44,868
[groans]

119
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:46,953
Bursting forth, Megamic Power!

120
00:04:46,995 --> 00:04:50,207
I gotta direct all
my mojo into my wings!

121
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:53,835
Ow! Oh my goddess, the pain!

122
00:04:53,877 --> 00:04:54,920
My poor flappers!

123
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:57,297
C'mon, Ristarte,
ya gotta dig deep!

124
00:04:57,339 --> 00:05:00,383
You can do it!
Put your wings into it!

125
00:05:01,384 --> 00:05:04,221
[RISTA sighs] Looks like Special
Measures of the Divine Realm

126
00:05:04,262 --> 00:05:06,431
aren't so special, huh?

127
00:05:08,809 --> 00:05:11,770
Such a princess. Honestly.

128
00:05:11,812 --> 00:05:14,189
Come on. Let's go.

129
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:15,315
[RISTA gasps]

130
00:05:19,945 --> 00:05:22,447
[RISTA]
Wow, he's such a gentleman.

131
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:25,367
He's even holding my hand!
It feels like we're on a date!

132
00:05:25,408 --> 00:05:26,201
[SEIYA]
Hey, Rista.

133
00:05:26,243 --> 00:05:28,036
Uh, yes, what is it?

134
00:05:28,078 --> 00:05:31,748
[RISTA] My name? Not the
usual "hey" or "hey, you"?

135
00:05:31,790 --> 00:05:33,124
Oh, you rascal.

136
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,918
Inter‐celestial
love is forbidden!

137
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:36,294
But I won't tell if you won't!

138
00:05:36,336 --> 00:05:39,881
[RISTA gasps] Wait, we could
totally be making out right now.

139
00:05:39,923 --> 00:05:41,967
What the crap,
I'm just gonna go for it.

140
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:43,510
I think we need
to speed it up.

141
00:05:43,552 --> 00:05:44,553
[RISTA gasps]

142
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:46,513
[RISTA shrieks]

143
00:05:46,555 --> 00:05:48,515
[RISTA]
Wh‐What the hell‐‐

144
00:05:48,557 --> 00:05:50,892
My goddess globes are loose!

145
00:05:50,934 --> 00:05:53,228
[RISTA yelling]

146
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:02,028
[RISTA panting]

147
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,655
I thought I was a goner!

148
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:05,740
You always forget
that you're immortal.

149
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:08,201
Funny though.
You sure look dead to me.

150
00:06:08,243 --> 00:06:10,120
And whose fault do
you think that is?

151
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:12,163
I've got bald spots
on my beautiful wings!

152
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:13,415
I look like I've been molting!

153
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:16,543
Can't you fix them with your
fancy‐pants healing magic?

154
00:06:16,585 --> 00:06:18,503
Anyway, shut your face‐hole.

155
00:06:18,545 --> 00:06:20,422
We don't want any
unexpected company.

156
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:21,339
Ugh!

157
00:06:21,381 --> 00:06:25,010
[UNDEAD groaning]

158
00:06:25,051 --> 00:06:25,844
[RISTA gasps]

159
00:06:25,886 --> 00:06:28,930
So they're marching as one
to show the Demon Lord's power.

160
00:06:28,972 --> 00:06:30,015
It's kind of impressive.

161
00:06:30,056 --> 00:06:31,266
So to be on the safe side,

162
00:06:31,308 --> 00:06:33,685
I'll break them up
before they get too far.

163
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:35,729
They won't survive
my bombardment.

164
00:06:35,770 --> 00:06:37,022
From what bombs though?

165
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:39,858
Rockets and missiles
don't exist in Gaeabrande.

166
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:42,027
Good thing I've learned
a skill to replace them.

167
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:44,446
Huh? With what exactly?

168
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:46,781
Hush and I'll show you.

169
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:51,453
What the‐‐ You're kidding me!

170
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:54,164
Who‐‐who hurt you?!

171
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:55,999
The Meteor Strike.

172
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:57,167
It's on the smaller side,

173
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:59,169
but if it falls at a
sufficiently high speed,

174
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:01,379
the collision will
be catastrophic.

175
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:03,298
Pure annihilation.

176
00:07:09,346 --> 00:07:10,305
Oh, okay.

177
00:07:10,347 --> 00:07:12,599
I kicked up the
energy towards the end.

178
00:07:12,641 --> 00:07:14,059
The moment it made impact,

179
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,102
it became superheated
and vaporized,

180
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:17,854
resulting in an explosion.

181
00:07:17,896 --> 00:07:19,105
Of course, yeah.

182
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:21,232
Oh. Although it's very powerful,

183
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:23,652
it's still a technique
with considerable limits.

184
00:07:23,693 --> 00:07:26,321
I can only use it in the open
and it takes a while to cast.

185
00:07:26,363 --> 00:07:30,825
So at what point did I miss
you learning to apocalypse?

186
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:32,577
[SEIYA]
When I was in the Divine Realm,

187
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:35,121
while making poop skirt cry.

188
00:07:35,163 --> 00:07:36,831
Of course, how could I forget?

189
00:07:36,873 --> 00:07:38,583
