234
00:09:30,278 --> 00:09:31,571
Rista...

235
00:09:33,156 --> 00:09:35,116
...come check this out.

236
00:09:35,158 --> 00:09:37,077
[RISTA]
A platinum sword?

237
00:09:37,118 --> 00:09:38,536
Huh. That's amazing!

238
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:40,580
What'd you do to
make this thing?

239
00:09:40,622 --> 00:09:41,873
[SEIYA]
Combining swords on their own

240
00:09:41,915 --> 00:09:43,792
didn't improve their
strength by much.

241
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:46,878
To forge a mighty weapon,
I needed something unique.

242
00:09:47,921 --> 00:09:50,590
And then, I found
a special catalyst.

243
00:09:50,632 --> 00:09:52,258
So what did you use?

244
00:09:53,343 --> 00:09:55,095
Blonde goddess hair!

245
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:56,596
[RISTA]
What?

246
00:09:56,638 --> 00:09:57,764
[SEIYA]
I found some in your room

247
00:09:57,806 --> 00:10:00,183
'cause you shed like
an old dying dog.

248
00:10:00,225 --> 00:10:02,102
A little this,
a little synthesizing it

249
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:03,728
with a steel blade...

250
00:10:04,813 --> 00:10:06,064
[SEIYA]
...and boom, you're welcome.

251
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:08,233
Wow. Lotta questions right now.

252
00:10:08,274 --> 00:10:10,902
But I'm glad you found
some part of me so useful.

253
00:10:10,944 --> 00:10:12,112
[SEIYA]
Hold onto that for me.

254
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:14,364
Also, I need more
hair. Like a lot.

255
00:10:14,405 --> 00:10:15,698
You can borrow my razor.

256
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:16,950
Do not use the sword.

257
00:10:16,991 --> 00:10:17,951
Shut up!

258
00:10:17,992 --> 00:10:19,202
‐‐[door opens]
‐‐[RISTA, ELULU] Huh?

259
00:10:19,244 --> 00:10:22,372
I've got a special
delivery for a hero!

260
00:10:22,413 --> 00:10:24,541
[SEIYA]
What is that? Who sent it here?

261
00:10:24,582 --> 00:10:26,835
A strange man wearing
a hood brought it over.

262
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:28,670
He said something about
wanting to give that

263
00:10:28,711 --> 00:10:31,422
"meathead hero" a gift?

264
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:34,467
That sounds fishy.
Could be an explosive.

265
00:10:34,509 --> 00:10:35,343
You open it.

266
00:10:35,385 --> 00:10:36,803
[RISTA]
Just because I can't die,

267
00:10:36,845 --> 00:10:39,681
doesn't mean you can
explosive boss me!

268
00:10:39,722 --> 00:10:40,807
[RISTA gasps]

269
00:10:41,850 --> 00:10:43,101
[RISTA]
Oh, my!

270
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:45,520
Who's that sexy little vixen?

271
00:10:49,983 --> 00:10:54,279
[gasping] I don't
like it anymore!

272
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,991
[BOTH gasp]

273
00:11:00,243 --> 00:11:01,703
No! This is bad!

274
00:11:01,744 --> 00:11:03,663
Mash is in trouble!

275
00:11:05,123 --> 00:11:07,125
[DEATHMAGLA]
Hello, can you see me?

276
00:11:07,167 --> 00:11:09,669
Do you hear the
sound of my voice?

277
00:11:09,711 --> 00:11:12,547
Well, I can see you all
perfectly from here.

278
00:11:12,589 --> 00:11:14,924
I spy a strappingly
handsome hero,

279
00:11:14,966 --> 00:11:16,634
a beautiful goddess in white,

280
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:19,262
and an adorable
young red‐haired girl.

281
00:11:20,388 --> 00:11:22,932
[DEATHMAGLA]
A peculiar mirror, is it not?

282
00:11:22,974 --> 00:11:24,767
It can reveal
images from far away

283
00:11:24,809 --> 00:11:26,853
through the magic
of the Demon Lord.

284
00:11:26,895 --> 00:11:29,147
Oops, I've yet to
introduce myself!

285
00:11:29,189 --> 00:11:32,275
My name is Deathmagla. I'm one
of the Four Heavenly Kings,

286
00:11:32,317 --> 00:11:35,695
and my unique specialty
is necromancy, of course.

287
00:11:35,737 --> 00:11:37,739
Whoa. That's the undead general?

288
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:40,325
What kinda general
doesn't march with his army?

289
00:11:40,366 --> 00:11:41,326
[DEATHMAGLA]
I must admit,

290
00:11:41,367 --> 00:11:45,288
I didn't expect you to
dispatch my minions so easily.

291
00:11:45,330 --> 00:11:48,666
Luckily, I was able to
command them remotely.

292
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:51,794
Speaking of that, do you
know how long it takes

293
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:54,297
to build a legion
of undead soldiers?

294
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:57,842
Obviously, I thought I'd
offset my losses with revenge

295
00:11:57,884 --> 00:12:00,428
with this weak,
milk smelling boy.

296
00:12:00,470 --> 00:12:03,765
No. Stop it! Leave him alone!

297
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:05,767
[DEATHMAGLA]
Working with corpses is tedious,

298
00:12:05,808 --> 00:12:08,269
but playing with
a life is so much fun.

299
00:12:08,311 --> 00:12:11,314
And when that gets boring,
there's always murder.

300
00:12:11,356 --> 00:12:13,483
[ELULU]
No, don't touch him! Please!

301
00:12:13,524 --> 00:12:15,401
[RISTA]
That's enough, you monster!

302
00:12:15,443 --> 00:12:16,527
[MASH grunting]

303
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:19,364
Oh, my, begging for
your life at the end?

304
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:22,992
Go right ahead and cry
as much as you like.

305
00:12:23,034 --> 00:12:24,577
Hey, hero.

306
00:12:24,619 --> 00:12:28,456
I heard you took out all
10,000 of those zombies.

307
00:12:28,498 --> 00:12:31,209
You're a big meathead
that's full of himself,

308
00:12:31,251 --> 00:12:33,127
but you're the real deal!

309
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:35,255
You're just different, you know?

310
00:12:35,296 --> 00:12:37,882
So please, no matter
what happens,

311
00:12:37,924 --> 00:12:39,717
you gotta save the world!

312
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:41,511
That poor boy.

313
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:44,264
[DEATHMAGLA] Come on, that
didn't sound like crying at all!

314
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:46,516
Fortunately, we won't
have to endure any

315
00:12:46,557 --> 00:12:49,018
of your baby blabbering
for much longer.

316
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:50,436
Somebody do something!

317
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:53,231
I'm begging you
to save him! Please!

318
00:12:53,273 --> 00:12:56,025
[cackles] Beg all you want!

319
00:12:56,067 --> 00:12:58,027
Your hero can't save him!

320
00:12:58,069 --> 00:13:01,948
All you can do is watch as
I slice through his neck!

321
00:13:01,990 --> 00:13:05,076
Rista, open a portal
to the Divine Realm.

322
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:08,496
But even if time is faster
there compared to Gaeabrande,

323
00:13:08,538 --> 00:13:09,372
what could we possibly do‐‐

324
00:13:09,414 --> 00:13:10,873
Just open it, now.

325
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:13,209
If you say so.

326
00:13:13,251 --> 00:13:15,920
I have to say, Mash.
You don't totally suck.

327
00:13:15,962 --> 00:13:17,588
Once we get you out of there,

328
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:19,716
I'm gonna let you
carry my gear for me.

329
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:21,009
[DEATHMAGLA]
Huh?

330
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:23,845
[SEIYA] Ya see, I've
already been here before.

331
00:13:25,263 --> 00:13:27,098
[SEIYA] Since then,
I've been running simulations

332
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:28,349
again and again.

333
00:13:28,391 --> 00:13:31,561
What if I had less time?
What would I do then?

334
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:35,356
Ha! Do you not understand
we aren't even in the same room?

335
00:13:35,398 --> 00:13:38,443
You stupid meathead!
You can't touch me!

336
00:13:38,484 --> 00:13:40,945
Stop it!

337
00:13:44,407 --> 00:13:46,075
[yells]

338
00:13:46,117 --> 00:13:48,911
[DEATHMAGLA]
No! B‐B‐But how?

339
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:51,748
Photon swords can cut
the fabric of space, bro.

340
00:13:51,789 --> 00:13:53,207
Meet my dimension blade.

341
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:56,377
Wh‐‐ According to what laws?
That thing is excessive‐‐

342
00:13:59,297 --> 00:14:02,050
Hurry up. The real
battle's just begun.

343
00:14:02,091 --> 00:14:03,801
[RISTA]
Huh? Care to explain?

344
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:05,887
We managed to confuse
him momentarily.

345
00:14:05,928 --> 00:14:08,848
But once he loses it,
he's gonna kill Mash.

346
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,350
Right! So what's the plan?

347
00:14:10,391 --> 00:14:13,019
As you know, time flows much
faster in the Divine Realm

348
00:14:13,061 --> 00:14:14,520
than it does back there.

349
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:16,606
It won't take tri‐clops
more than ten seconds

350
00:14:16,647 --> 00:14:19,609
to find a weapon and
shank dragonboy with it.

351
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:22,362
Therefore, we have
less than 15 minutes

352
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:26,199
to figure out how to get to
them first and rescue our guy.

353
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:28,451
'Kay, I think I got it.

354
00:14:28,493 --> 00:14:30,828
I might know someone
who can help, but...

355
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:34,123
...let me lead.
You just need to stay quiet!

356
00:14:34,165 --> 00:14:36,292
[SEIYA] Granny, are you
the head goddess around here?

357
00:14:36,334 --> 00:14:38,503
Hey! Didn't I tell
you to shut your mouth?

358
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:40,922
Sorry! Ishtar! So sorry!
I really mean it...

359
00:14:40,963 --> 00:14:43,549
I'm looking for Shrooms on
Gaeabrande and it's urgent.

360
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:44,509
Bust out a portal.

361
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:47,303
[RISTA] That is not how you
speak to a Great Goddess!

362
00:14:47,345 --> 00:14:49,597
And no more fungus puns!
His name is Mash!

363
00:14:49,639 --> 00:14:51,849
[chuckles] So in other words,

364
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:54,936
you're saying you'd like me to
help you find your companion.

365
00:14:54,977 --> 00:14:57,105
But divine law forbids goddesses

366
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:59,941
from granting any excessive
support to humankind.

367
00:14:59,982 --> 00:15:01,901
All you'd be doing
is making a hole‐‐

368
00:15:01,943 --> 00:15:05,071
a door in a specific spot, like
this chick does all the time.

369
00:15:05,113 --> 00:15:07,073
Totes no big.

370
00:15:07,115 --> 00:15:08,449
True, true.

371
00:15:08,491 --> 00:15:11,327
I do believe you might
just have a point there.

372
00:15:11,369 --> 00:15:12,870
Very well, then.

373
00:15:15,998 --> 00:15:17,458
Ah. There it is.

374
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:19,544
They're in the forest
near Krain Castle.

375
00:15:19,585 --> 00:15:22,338
Your friend is being held
captive in a vast dungeon.

376
00:15:22,380 --> 00:15:24,757
Thanks. You're always
incredible, Ishtar!

377
00:15:24,799 --> 00:15:26,634
[SEIYA]
Good. Now, drop us in.

378
00:15:26,676 --> 00:15:28,219
Right in front of
the Mashed Potato.

379
00:15:28,261 --> 00:15:29,178
Okay.

380
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:31,889
Great, now we're doing potatoes.

381
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:35,893
Thank you for helping us.
We'd be lost without your aid!

382
00:15:35,935 --> 00:15:37,145
C'mon, say something!

383
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:39,021
Hey, good job. Thanks, mee‐maw.

384
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:41,274
Can you not be smug
for five seconds?! Ugh!

385
00:15:41,315 --> 00:15:43,234
Do you even know what
you're walking us into?

386
00:15:43,276 --> 00:15:45,361
Duh, what do you take me for?

387
00:15:45,403 --> 00:15:47,238
As soon as we exit the portal,

388
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:49,282
I'm hitting him
with Hell's Fire.

389
00:15:49,323 --> 00:15:52,702
While he's distracted, you can
use the moment to scoop up Mash.

390
00:15:52,743 --> 00:15:55,538
‐‐[SEIYA] Let's go.
‐‐Uh, roger that.

391
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:01,878
It's impressive how much you've
grown, Mister Seiya Ryuuguuin.

392
00:16:01,919 --> 00:16:03,504
I bid you good hunting.

393
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,633
[DEATHMAGLA]
Ah! It hurts!

394
00:16:07,675 --> 00:16:11,137
My hand! But how?!

395
00:16:11,179 --> 00:16:15,766
[DEATHMAGLA groaning]

396
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:16,893
Huh?

397
00:16:16,934 --> 00:16:19,270
Miss me? Hell's Fire!

398
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:23,065
[DEATHMAGLA yelps]

399
00:16:23,107 --> 00:16:24,901
Hey, it's Rista! You okay?

400
00:16:24,942 --> 00:16:27,612
I... think so.

401
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,989
[RISTA gasps]
Oh, how heartless!

402
00:16:30,031 --> 00:16:31,240
Let's get you patched up!

403
00:16:31,282 --> 00:16:33,117
[MASH groans]

404
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:36,787
[RISTA]
How's he doing?

405
00:16:36,829 --> 00:16:37,997
[gasps]

406
00:16:41,751 --> 00:16:43,294
[RISTA]
Black flames?

407
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:45,796
It looks like the fire
is protecting him!

408
00:16:51,761 --> 00:16:54,347
Whoa. What kind of
monster is that?

409
00:16:54,388 --> 00:16:56,224
[MASH gasps]
It's...

410
00:16:56,265 --> 00:16:57,475
It's a‐‐

411
00:16:58,476 --> 00:17:01,521
Was that all it took to
take down Chaos Machina?

412
00:17:01,562 --> 00:17:03,606
Because it won't work
on this Heavenly King.

413
00:17:03,648 --> 00:17:05,149
Your weakness is insulting!

414
00:17:05,191 --> 00:17:06,317
[SEIYA grunts]

415
00:17:08,945 --> 00:17:12,615
Is that a ghost monster?
Seiya, holy water!

416
00:17:12,657 --> 00:17:14,992
I already tried that
stuff. It didn't work.

417
00:17:15,034 --> 00:17:17,161
Oh, right. I bet that
was your first move.

418
00:17:17,203 --> 00:17:19,080
Hold up. So it's not a ghost?

419
00:17:19,121 --> 00:17:21,582
[DEATHMAGLA]
This one's name is Dark Firus‐‐

420
00:17:21,624 --> 00:17:23,167
the mightiest, fieriest creature

421
00:17:23,209 --> 00:17:26,212
I've ever created out of
my hundreds of experiments.

422
00:17:26,254 --> 00:17:29,674
A fire‐type? I thought
you only created the undead!

423
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:31,759
Modifying all manner of monsters

424
00:17:31,801 --> 00:17:35,680
just so happens to be my special
skill, you basic simpleton!

425
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:37,181
Who ya callin' basic?!

426
00:17:37,223 --> 00:17:39,892
We need to exploit
his weaknesses!

427
00:17:39,934 --> 00:17:42,436
D‐Defense is over
a hundred thousand?

428
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,689
He's immune to
all weapon attacks?

429
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,399
Only weak against ice magic?

430
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,651
Yes, you blonde idiot!

431
00:17:48,693 --> 00:17:51,821
You fight it by disrupting
its molecular structure

432
00:17:51,862 --> 00:17:55,074
with the Oscillatory Wave skill.

433
00:17:55,116 --> 00:17:58,703
Cold attacks will convert its
affiliation from fire to ice,

434
00:17:58,744 --> 00:18:01,622
making its ghostly
body materialize.

435
00:18:01,664 --> 00:18:04,500
If you can hit Dark Firus with
a power that's greater than

436
00:18:04,542 --> 00:18:08,045
its defense, only then
can you defeat it!

437
00:18:08,087 --> 00:18:11,549
[SEIYA] Huh. Thanks for
the boss walkthrough, pops.

438
00:18:11,591 --> 00:18:12,883
[RISTA]
Hold on.

439
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:15,886
Oscillatory Wave is
a melee‐only technique.

440
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:19,390
And ice spells are the complete
opposite of Seiya's fire magic!

441
00:18:19,432 --> 00:18:20,891
There's no way to beat him!

442
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:22,268
[DEATHMAGLA]
I fed you bits of hope

443
00:18:22,310 --> 00:18:25,354
so I could savor every
moment of your despair!

444
00:18:25,396 --> 00:18:28,107
I have hypothesized
every contingency

445
00:18:28,149 --> 00:18:29,233
and planned accordingly,

446
00:18:29,275 --> 00:18:32,820
for that's the genius
of a true tactician!

447
00:18:34,071 --> 00:18:35,573
[SEIYA]
Is this really happening?

448
00:18:35,615 --> 00:18:37,074
[RISTA]
Pretty much.

449
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:38,492
How surprising.

450
00:18:38,534 --> 00:18:40,286
I'm kinda shocked, honestly.

451
00:18:40,328 --> 00:18:41,912
[RISTA gasps]

452
00:18:41,954 --> 00:18:44,040
[SEIYA] You say you've done
a lot of hypothesizing

453
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:45,750
and planning? Nah.

454
00:18:45,791 --> 00:18:49,003
You act so pretentious, but I
can read you like an open book.

455
00:18:49,045 --> 00:18:51,339
Are you implying you've
somehow anticipated

456
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:53,341
this exact situation?

457
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:55,301
[SEIYA]
I'm implying you're a huge tool

458
00:18:55,343 --> 00:18:57,637
and you've already
lost and don't know it.

459
00:18:57,678 --> 00:19:00,806
Nice talk, sugar lips,
but you won't defeat him!

460
00:19:00,848 --> 00:19:05,061
He's invincible and you're a sad
excuse for an unprepared hero!

461
00:19:05,102 --> 00:19:07,438
[cackles]

462
00:19:07,480 --> 00:19:08,397
[SEIYA]
That's not my style.

463
00:19:08,439 --> 00:19:09,523
Huh?

464
00:19:11,692 --> 00:19:13,611
I am perfectly prepared.

465
00:19:13,653 --> 00:19:16,364
I'm 100 percent
ready for this fight!

466
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:21,202
Ha! I'm ready to wipe that smug
look off your dumb emo face!

467
00:19:21,243 --> 00:19:23,245
[DARK FIRUS growls]

468
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:24,288
[DARK FIRUS yells]

469
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:26,749
[RISTA gasps]
Wait, what?

470
00:19:26,791 --> 00:19:27,625
[DEATHMAGLA]
Behold!

471
00:19:27,667 --> 00:19:30,628
A fire that won't burn
out till it consumes you!

472
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:33,964
Dodge if you wish, but everyone
behind you will perish instead!

473
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:36,175
Ahh, that means us...

474
00:19:36,217 --> 00:19:40,221
Don't need to dodge you.
Go ahead and do your worst.

475
00:19:40,262 --> 00:19:42,390
You still dare to attack me?

476
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:43,432
Dark‐‐

477
00:19:44,475 --> 00:19:46,852
[DARK FIRUS groans]

478
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:48,270
[RISTA]
The Oscillatory Wave!

479
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:50,690
[DEATHMAGLA] That's impossible!
You're a swordsman.

480
00:19:50,731 --> 00:19:53,150
How do you have a melee skill?

481
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:55,319
[SEIYA] I don't believe
in limiting myself.

482
00:19:55,361 --> 00:19:56,862
If I couldn't use my blade,

483
00:19:56,904 --> 00:19:59,657
then I'd have to use my fists.

484
00:19:59,699 --> 00:20:02,159
Some enemies are
resistant to sword attacks.

485
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:05,121
And there's no telling when
it might break during combat.

486
00:20:05,162 --> 00:20:07,206
What if it got
stolen by my opponents?

487
00:20:07,248 --> 00:20:08,499
Or what if it got rusted?

488
00:20:08,541 --> 00:20:11,001
Or dissolved?
Or got eaten by moths?

489
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:13,170
It's a good thing I learned
hand‐to‐hand combat.

490
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:16,340
Okay, that is
unbelievably cautious.

491
00:20:16,382 --> 00:20:19,885
Doesn't matter, because you're
still no match for Dark Firus

492
00:20:19,927 --> 00:20:22,388
and his burning fists
of fiery death!

493
00:20:22,430 --> 00:20:24,014
[DARK FIRUS yelling]

494
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,307
[DEATHMAGLA]
You think you can counter

495
00:20:25,349 --> 00:20:27,268
with your puny human hands?

496
00:20:27,309 --> 00:20:29,854
Your whole arm will explode!

497
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:33,607
Wait! What is happening?

498
00:20:33,649 --> 00:20:36,068
Fire and ice magic
are incompatible!

499
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:39,989
There's no way you should
be able to use both!

500
00:20:40,030 --> 00:20:41,323
[gasps] That amulet!

501
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:44,785
An item that grants
the properties of ice?

502
00:20:44,827 --> 00:20:45,953
[RISTA]
That's it!

503
00:20:45,995 --> 00:20:47,580
Even if he can't
produce it on his own,

504
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:49,373
he can achieve the same effect!

505
00:20:49,415 --> 00:20:51,876
Wait, where'd he find something
like that to begin with?

506
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:52,668
[RISTA gasps]

507
00:20:52,710 --> 00:20:55,588
Synthesis! You made
that bracelet yourself!

508
00:20:55,629 --> 00:20:56,797
Yeah.

509
00:20:56,839 --> 00:21:00,342
Nice! But what did you
synthesize to make that?

510
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:04,096
I just used an ordinary bangle,
a few ice cubes, and your hair.

511
00:21:04,138 --> 00:21:06,599
‐‐[RISTA] Uh... Huh?
‐‐Yeah, your hair made it work.

512
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:08,851
Oh. There's more
where that came from.

513
00:21:08,893 --> 00:21:09,685
[RISTA]
Huh?

514
00:21:09,727 --> 00:21:12,104
Some for lightning,
some for light, some for dark,

515
00:21:12,146 --> 00:21:14,774
and of course the list
goes on. I made spares, too.

516
00:21:14,815 --> 00:21:16,817
And yes all of them
synthesized from hairs

517
00:21:16,859 --> 00:21:18,319
that were scattered
around your bedroom.

518
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:19,737
[RISTA]
That's a lot of hair.

519
00:21:19,779 --> 00:21:21,864
Oh my gosh, I'm not
going bald, am I?

520
00:21:21,906 --> 00:21:23,824
Only his body materialized.

521
00:21:23,866 --> 00:21:25,701
You and your stupid hairs

522
00:21:25,743 --> 00:21:28,162
still can't overcome
Dark Firus's defenses!

523
00:21:28,204 --> 00:21:30,164
You're right.
Unfortunately, I don't.

524
00:21:30,206 --> 00:21:31,874
But it's no problem.

525
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:32,958
You know what's
effective against

526
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:35,920
a vulnerable,
glistening body of ice?

527
00:21:35,961 --> 00:21:37,129
A flame attack.

528
00:21:37,171 --> 00:21:38,923
Whoopsie! Didn't think of that!

529
00:21:38,964 --> 00:21:41,467
Dark Firus, close in
and stop his attack!

530
00:21:41,509 --> 00:21:43,177
It's too late.

531
00:21:46,764 --> 00:21:49,308
[SEIYA]
A white‐hot, fixed‐point strike!

532
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:51,185
Phoenix Thrust!

533
00:21:59,568 --> 00:22:01,070
[RISTA]
Thrusted it!

534
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:02,363
Is he for real?

535
00:22:02,404 --> 00:22:04,824
He just demolished that
behemoth like it was nothing!

536
00:22:04,865 --> 00:22:06,075
Eat it, sucker!

537
00:22:06,116 --> 00:22:08,661
That's a one in a hundred
million phenomenon over there!

538
00:22:08,702 --> 00:22:10,996
No, no, no! There's no way!

539
00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:14,375
[RISTA] That's what you get for
monologuing yourself, you loser!

540
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:16,585
Well, if he hadn't
told us how to win,

541
00:22:16,627 --> 00:22:18,712
I'm sure I would've
found out soon enough.

542
00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:20,256
Yeah! I believe you!

543
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:22,967
Because you're the smartest
and strongest hero ever!

544
00:22:23,008 --> 00:22:23,884
Now then.

545
00:22:23,926 --> 00:22:26,303
It's time for me to finish
taking out the trash.

546
00:22:26,345 --> 00:22:27,888
[DEATHMAGLA gasps]

547
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:34,395
[SEIYA] After that,
this room needs a deep clean.

548
00:22:34,436 --> 00:22:37,773
[whimpering]

549
00:22:37,815 --> 00:22:39,191
You go right ahead.

550
00:22:39,233 --> 00:22:41,944
Take all the time
you need, okay?

551
00:22:43,904 --> 00:22:46,657
[DEATHMAGLA screams]

